OL,3,CThe AI technology changing the way
OL,4,Cpolice fight crime
OL,6,FCampaigners are worried however what
OL,7,Fthis new technology may mean for civil
OL,8,Fliberties. They argue it runs the risk
OL,9,Fof turning the country into a "mass
OL,10,Fsurveillance state", can lead to
OL,11,Fmisidentification and lacks any
OL,12,Fspecific laws governing its use.
OL,14,FThis year, the Met Police has deployed
OL,15,FLFR tech more than 160 times. We
OL,16,Fjoined its officers in Croydon, South
OL,17,FLondon to see how it worked.
OL,19,FThe cameras themselves are attached to
OL,20,Fthe top of a police van scanning all
OL,21,Fdirections of the high street.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
